cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.AI. 

This paper discusses Prolog's support for domain specific languages, meta programming, and text processing, which are all topics related to programming languages and software engineering. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are likely categories. The paper also discusses context-free grammars, which are commonly used in natural language processing, suggesting cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another possible category. The use of quasi-quoting for text processing and embedding external languages may also relate to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) possible categories as well.
